snippet.textDisplay: The part two girl were signing is a special genre of music born in northern Bengal (Rangpur, Dinajpur, Thakurgaon etc) , the genre is called Bhaoaiya (Bhaa-o-aa-i--ya). This genre of music is dated as back as the reign of sena dynasty. Jayadeva, the famous Sanskrit poet and author of Gita Govinda, has wrote about a certain type of music being practiced in northern Bengal and wrote "They call it Bhavaya".  Some Bengali authors believe that Jayadeva was one of the Pancharatnas (five gems) in the court of Lakshmana Sena.
